\section2 The File Menu

This menu is invoked with \Key Alt+F, and provides the following
options:
\list

\i \Menu File|New Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+N) to
create a new project, form or file. This option invokes the
\l{The New Form Dialog}.

*\i \Menu File|Open Click this menu option (or press\Key Ctrl+O) to
open existing projects, forms or files. The \l{Open Dialog} appears and
the file name and type
must be selected.

\i \Menu File|Close Click this menu option to close the project that
is currently open. If changes are made to the project and it has not
been saved previously or if the project name begins with the word
'unnamed', the \l{Save Form Dialog} appears.

\i \Menu File|Save  Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+S) to
save the project. The \l{Save As Dialog} appears for any forms or
files that have file names that begin with the word 'unnamed'. ##If
the project has already been given a name, then 'Save' will save it to
that name without invoking a Dialog. 

*\i \Menu {File|Save As} Click this menu option to save and name the project.
This option invokes the \l{Save As Dialog}.

\i \Menu {File|Save All} Click this menu option to save every open
file in every open project.

*\i \Menu {File|Create Template} Click this menu option to create a
form template. This option invokes the \l{Create Template}
dialog.

\i \Menu {File|Recently Opened Files} Click this menu option to list the most
recently opened files. Click one of the files listed to open it. Note
that we recommend that you open projects rather than files. You can
open a file by clicking the file's name in the project's \l{File Overview Window}.

\i \Menu {File|Recently Opened Projects}  Click this menu option to list the most
recently opened projects. Click one of the projects listed to open it. 

\i \Menu File|Exit Click this menu option to exit \QD. If any open
files have unsaved changes, the \l{Save Form} message box will appear
for each of them, before \QD exits. Note that if any open projects
have any files that begin with the word 'unnamed', the \l{Save Form As
dialog} will appear for each of these files. If any open project's
name begins with the word 'unnamed' the \l{Save Project Settings}
message box appears.  

\section3 The Edit Menu

This menu is invoked with \Key Alt+E, and provides the following
options:
\list

\i \Menu Edit|Undo Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+Z) to
undo an action. The name of the last action that was performed appears
after the word 'Undo' in this menu option. 

\i \Menu Edit|Redo Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+Y) to
redo an action.The name of the last action that was performed appears
after the word 'Redo' in this menu option.

\i \Menu Edit|Cut Click
this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+X) to delete the selected item
from the current form or file and copy it to the clipboard.

\i \Menu Edit|Copy Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+C) to copy the selected
item from the current form or file to the clipboard.

\i \Menu Edit|Paste Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+V) to paste the
selected item from the clipboard into the current form or file.

\i \Menu Edit|Delete Click this menu option (or press \Key Del) to delete the selected
item from the current form or file.

\i \Menu {Edit|Select All} Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+A) to highlight all
the widgets on the current form or all the text in the current file. 

\i \Menu {Edit|Check Accelerator} Click this menu option (or press
\Key Alt+R) to verify that all the accelerators are used only
once.If an accelerator is used more than once, a message box
appears with the statement 'The accelerator 'x' is used 'y' times',
where 'X' is the accelerator and 'y' is the number of times it is
used. Click 'Select' to highlightthe widgets with the same
accelerator, or click 'Cancel' to exit the message box without any
action. 

*\i \Menu Edit|Slots Click this menu option to edit or create slots which
are used in conjunction with signals to provide communication between
two objects. This option invokes the \l{Edit Slots Dialog}.

*\i \Menu Edit|Connections Click this menu option to invoke the \l{View
Connections Dialog}. 

\i \Menu {Edit|Form Settings}  Click this menu option to invoke the \l{Form
Settings Dialog} ###which allows you to change the settings, pixmap,
and layout properties of the form.

*\i \Menu Edit|Preferences Click this menu option to invoke the
\l{Preferences Dialog}.

\section4 The Project Menu

This menu is invoked with \Key Alt+O, and provides the following
options:
\list 

\i \Menu {Project|Active Project|\<project name\>}  Click this menu
option to toggle between projects if there is more than one project
open.

*\i \Menu{Project|Add File} Click this menu option 
 to invoke the \l{Add Dialog} which allows you to
add files from any location and insert them into the project you are
working on.

*\i \Menu {Project|Project Settings}  Click this menu option to change
the project settings by invoking the \l{Project Settings
Dialog}.

*\i \Menu {Project|Image Collection}  Click this menu option to invoke
the \l{Edit Image Collection Dialog}, which allows you to add or
edit images imported from any location and use them in the current
project.

*\i \Menu {Project|Database Connections}  Click this menu option to
invoke the \l{Edit Database Connections Dialog} which allows you
to connect your project to a database or to edit the current
connection.

\section5 The Search Menu

This menu is invoked with \Key Alt+S, and provides the following
options:
\list

*\i \Menu Search|Find Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+F) to invoke the \l{Find
Text} Dialog which is used to locate specific words or characters
in the files. 

\i \Menu {Search|Find Incremental} Click this menu option (or press
\Key Alt+I) to place the cursor in the text box located next to the
\Toolbutton Find toolbar button. Type characters into the text box; as
you type \QD will highlight the first occurrence of the text that it
finds in the file. Press the \Key Enter key to go to the next
occurrence of the text.

*\i \Menu Search|Replace Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+R)
to invoke the \l{Replace Text} Dialog to replace specific
words or characters.

*\i \Menu{Search|Goto line} Click this menu option (or press \Key
Alt+G) to invoke the \l{Goto Line Dialog} to go to a specific line
in the file.

